body:
I have the following code (parsing the contents of `/proc/meminfo`):

```rust
                for line in reader {
                    // Split the line at the `:`
                    let split = line.expect("unable to read procfs").split(":");

                    let name = split.next().expect("Malformed input").trim(); // ERROR temporary in "split" is reused
                    let value = split.next().expect("Malformed input").trim();

                    map.insert(name, value);
                }
```

I correctly get an error that the temporary created for the first part of the expression in `split`'s RHS is reused on the following line.

However, the error message says that the borrow is used in a _later iteration of the loop_, which is false. The temporary is used later in the _same_ iteration.

```
error[E0716]: temporary value dropped while borrowed
   --> src/linux4_4/procfs/meminfo.rs:82:33
    |
82  |                       let split = line.expect("unable to read procfs").split(":");
    |                                   ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^           - temporary value is freed at the end of this statement
    |                                   |
    |                                   creates a temporary which is freed while still in use
83  |
84  |                       let name = split.next().expect("Malformed input").trim();
    |                                  ----- borrow used here, in later iteration of loop
```
